{"lemma":"مَسْنُونٌ","slug":"مَسْنُونٌ","root":"س.ن.ن","root_slug":"س-ن-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ن-ن","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَسْنُون","root":"سنن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20868"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pointy, sharpened"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"enacted, passed, legislated"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"molded, shaped, formed"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of مُسِنّ (musinn)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of سَنَّ (sanna).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/mas.nuːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20868","headword_ar":"مَسْنُونٌ","root":"sn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bitten with the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, app., what next follows]. You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN masonuwnapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ مَسْنُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saniynN","text_ar":"سَنِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land of which the herbage has been eaten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharpened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whetted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made sharp-pointed, and polished;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saniynN","text_ar":"سَنِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, L, K;) applied to a knife (K) or thing [of any kind]. (M, L.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Made smooth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Formed, fashioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shaped."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Made long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajohN masonuwnN","text_ar":"وَجْهٌ مَسْنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A face in which is length, without breadth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxorwuTN","text_ar":"مَخْروُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth and even;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth and long;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long, and not high in the ball;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, tender, thin, and even;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the flesh were ground ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sun~a","text_ar":"سُنَّ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1440},{"kind":"text","text":"[like as a thing is ground in sharpening and polishing]) from it. (M, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN masonuwnu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ مَسْنُونُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwajohi","text_ar":"الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man beautiful and smooth in the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man in whose nose and face is length:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful and long in the face."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino HamaA^ masonuwnK","text_ar":"مِنْ حَمَا مَسْنُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xv. 26 and 28 and 33], (L,) means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of black mud"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the worse in odour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (AA, S, L;) in which sense"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masonuwn","text_ar":"مَسْنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to water; (AHeyth, L;) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stinking:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, M, L, K:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sananotu AlHajara EalaY AlHajari","text_ar":"سَنَنْتُ الحَجَرَ عَلَى الحَجَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I rubbed, or grated, the stone upon the stone; ” what flows between them, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saniyn","text_ar":"سَنِين"},{"kind":"text","text":", being always stinking: (Ksh and Bd in xv. 26: [and the like is said in the L, on the authority of Fr:]) or, accord. to I'Ab, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord to AO,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured forth in a form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shape:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formed, fashioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shaped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured forth in order to its drying"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardening"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and becoming formed, fashioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shaped, like as molten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liquified, substances are poured forth into moulds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, * Bd.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Lh","M","L","S","AA","Ksh","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}